Vice President Kamala Harris delivered a speech at the Kennedy Center in Washington, D.C., addressing the rise of hate crimes in the United States. She emphasized the need for reflection and action to combat this epidemic of hate, which manifests in acts of violence. Harris called for unity and the mobilization of various groups to fight against hate and incitement of violence. She praised the work of the AAPI Victory Fund in mobilizing voters and highlighted the importance of Asian American and Pacific Islander (AAPI) voices in shaping policies. Harris also discussed the progress made by the administration in areas such as job creation, infrastructure, and diversity in government appointments. She urged AAPI communities to make their voices heard in the upcoming midterm elections, as they were crucial in the 2020 elections. Harris emphasized the importance of ensuring equal opportunities for all and creating a more just and inclusive future for the country.